The paper discusses a novel learning framework for constructing provably correct neural networks with respect to safety properties. This involves integrating an optimization-based abstraction refinement loop into the learning process, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with safety properties, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of optimization-based abstraction refinement loop also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY) or software engineering (cs.SE).
